duck: Monic languages - The Monic languages are a branch of the Austroasiatic language family descended from the Old Monic language of the kingdom of Dvaravati in what is now central Thailand.
monic polynomial - a polynomial whose leading coefficient is one.
monic morphism - a special kind of morphism in category theory.
In mathematics, monic can refer to monic morphism - a special kind of morphism in category theory.
